        "name": "Trilobite",
        "sections": [
          {
            "name": "Tremendous Variety",
            "sources": [
              {
                "link": {
                  "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 326",
                  "aonid": 276,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 326",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "Monster Core 2",
                "page": 326,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Scholars of the sea have identified thousands of varieties of trilobites, each distinguished by appearance, habitat, size, and diet. The smallest trilobites are an inch or two long, while individuals measuring almost 2 feet long have been found in the depths of the ocean. Some hide in silt, using tall eyestalks to spot prey, while others have wide, sweeping, winglike heads; certain kinds are even covered in spines. This variety in appearance has led to distinctive jewelry in seaside villages that imitates local trilobite populations.",
            "type": "section"
          }
        ],
        "sources": [
          {
            "link": {
              "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 326",
              "aonid": 276,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 326",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Monster Core 2",
            "page": 326,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Often overlooked as little more than water-dwelling pests, trilobites are a varied class of arthropods found throughout the seas and oceans of Golarion. So ancient and widespread are these critters that trilobite fossils are as commonly found as living specimens.  \n  \n Trilobites vary wildly in both size and diet, with the largest reaching up to 28 inches long. Fossil record shows that trilobites were even more diverse and prevalent in ancient times than they are today, but their species entered a decline due to the devastation of Earthfall.",
        "type": "monster_family"
      },
